com.password4j

Class Password

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.password4j.Password

  • public class Password
extends Object
    This class provides the two main operations on password: hash and verify.

    All the methods are static because there's no sense to have an instance of Password. It represents a facade layer that ease the usage of the package itself and so this should be the only class to be invoked from this package.

    Since:
    0.1.1
    Author:
    David Bertoldi

        public static HashBuilder hash(CharSequence plainTextPassword)

        This method is used to start the setup of a HashBuilder instance that finally should execute the HashBuilder.with(HashingFunction) method to hash the password.

      • check

        public static boolean check(CharSequence plainTextPassword,
                            Hash hashObject)
        Starts to verify if an hash object has been generated with the given plain text password.

        This method uses the HashingFunction used to calculate the given Hash. Il the password is null, this returns false; otherwise HashingFunction.check(CharSequence, String) is invoked.

        Parameters:
        plainTextPassword - the original password.
        hashObject - an Hash object.
        Returns:
        true if the check passes, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        BadParametersException - if the Hash is null or if there's no hashing function defined in it.
        Since:
        1.0.3

      • hash

        public static <B extends HashBuilder<?>> B hash(CharSequence plainTextPassword,
                                                Function<CharSequence,B> builderFunction)
        Starts to hash the given plain text password with a custom builder.

        This method is used to start the setup of a HashBuilder instance that finally should execute the HashBuilder.with(HashingFunction) method (or an equivalent method) to hash the password.

        The extended HashBuilder is built with a Function because it is easier to invoke, rather than call the constructor with the same argument.

        For example:
        Passowrd.hash("password", CustomHashBuilder::new);

        Parameters:
        plainTextPassword - the plain text password
        builderFunction - any lambda function or method reference that returns an instance of the extended HashBuilder.
        Returns:
        a builder instance of HashBuilder
        Throws:
        BadParametersException - if any of the arguments are null.
        Since:
        0.1.1

      • check

        public static <C extends HashChecker<?>> C check(CharSequence plainTextPassword,
                                                 String hash,
                                                 BiFunction<CharSequence,String,C> checkerBiFunction)
        Verify if an hash string has been generated with the given plain text password with a custom verifier.

        This method is used to start the setup of a custom HashChecker instance that finally should execute the HashChecker.with(HashingFunction) (or an equivalent method) to verify the hash.

        The extended HashChecker is built with a BiFunction because it is easier to invoke, rather than call the constructor with the same two arguments.

        For example:
        Passowrd.check("password", "hash", CustomHashChecker::new);

        Parameters:
        plainTextPassword - the plain text password
        hash - an hash string
        checkerBiFunction - any lambda function or method reference that returns an instance of the extended HashChecker.
        Returns:
        a builder instance of HashChecker
        Throws:
        BadParametersException - if any of the arguments are null.
        Since:
        0.2.1
